[src:helmet-security/http-headers] HTTP range requests allow the client to request a portion of a resource from the server.
[src:helmet-security/http-headers] Range requests are useful for applications like media players that support random access, data tools that know they need only part of a large file, and download managers that let the user pause and resume a download.
